"What a fantastic beer! Slightly less intense than the 90 and 120 minutes, yet strong enough for hop heads to get their fix. It pours a light copper with a modest sized head that retains as a soapy, creamy and frothy looking lace. The aroma is great; malt sweetness, some cocoa and especially floral hops. It almost smells like a perfume! Taste has a strong malt backbone to balance off the hops intensity. The finish is dry and bitter. Amazing feel; creamy, crisp, refreshing and unbelievably drinkable. DFH is the best!!"
