"O: Balance. The idea of continual hopping is to preserve the hop flavor while preventing the hop astringency. Sam does a swell job with this one. Anxious to try the 90 and 120."
"Pours a light clear light copper/orange with a 2 finger head and a fair amount of head and retention. Slight grapefruit, mango and peach on the nose, with a nice caramel malt backbone. Citrus and malt bang on the tongue, grassy and earth with a nice bitter finish. Light to medium on body, medium carbonation that gives a tingly champagne feel, that ends sweet and bitter. Overall DFH 60 is a typical ""East Coast"" IPA, its big on malt even when fresh, and has nice hop characteristics to boot. Good beer, always available, but not knocking any socks off."
