"On draft at the Coffee District. Just a solid IPA, would recommend this beer to any IPA drinker. Nice lacing. Aroma is of rich, fruity hops - citrus, grapefruit, and mango. Caramel malt comes through a bit along with some breadiness - kind of bread crust-like. Flavor is of clementine, lemon, and grapefruit with some pine. The malt is lighter than in the aroma - mainly caramel malt and light toast. Medium body with moderate carbonation. Pleasantly sweet with a pronounced hop bitterness at the end. Lingering, bitter finish with a touch of resin that avoids being unpleasant. Overall a really great IPA that is solid and repeatable."
"I'm not an IPA person for the most part, but this is one IPA that I'll always reach for. Go buy a pint, 6 pk, or a case... it's a keeper"
