"Moderate carbonation. About 3/8 inch of ivory head that dissipates in about 30 seconds. Sparse suds remain when lacing stimulated or sipped. Most notable smells, in additional to low-moderate hops and medium malt, are pine, floral and citrus (perhaps grapefruit, orange and lemon). A relatively mild nose. Carbonation is great upon tasting. Medium body and moderate bitterness (think pale ale). Aftertaste of pine and mild hoppiness. An ideal, hoppy second stage aftertaste expected of top-tier classic IPAs. A delightfully refreshing beverage. Very drinkable. An IPA that is content to earn approval and respect over a session rather than at first sip."
