"Draft, City Beer Store. Good IPA. I like this more than expected. It has a nice honey, citrus and pine aroma. Good looking beer - medium gold with a healthy white cap. The taste has a bit of malt extract flavor but is otherwise pleasing. It's fairly dry which is a nice change of pace for DFH. Not quite enough bitter bite in the finish. It could use a bit more hops, though they're certainly present and I'm probably being a bit of an IPA snob by saying that. Mouth feel is unobjectionable. Nice IPA. This is one of my favorites from DFH."
