"The separate characters of the bittering, aroma and dry hops are indistinguishable, and pass smoothly from one note to the next in the palate. Even the flavors of the different hops used are transposed. And unlike many other IPAs, which tend to be all oars and no boat, this IPA has a very strong but silent ""beer"" foundation with toasty and malty flavors which holds all 60-minutes of hops together. This beer sets a new bar, and sets it high."
