"Served from a 12 oz bottle. Pours out a very clear amber color, capped with a voluminous head consisting of tight white bubbles. Aroma is hoppy to the point of being almost frightening, a very interesting mix of piney hops and frsh mown grass, there's a certain sharpness to it that you don't find in most IPA's. Taste is drenched with acidic grapefruit hop flavor and a strong pine as well. There's something different in the nose and flavor that adds a certain herbal tang, that I'm still trying to put a finger on. Nice sweet malt flavor comes along mid-way through, but it cannot compete with the hops. You're left with a resounding bitterness that keeps going and going. Definitely another unique IPA from the Dogfish family, worth a try."
